  "notes": [
    {
      "title": "Conditional Sentences (الشرط)",
      "titleArabic": "أسلوب الشرط",
      "content": [
        "Conditional sentences in Arabic consist of a condition (شرط) and a result (جواب الشرط). Different particles are used for different types of conditions.",
        "The main conditional particles are: إِنْ (if), إِذَا (when/if), and لَوْ (if - hypothetical)."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "إِنْ - 'if' (jussive): Both verbs become مجزوم",
        "إِذَا - 'when/if' (past tense): Used with past tense verbs",
        "لَوْ - 'if' (hypothetical/unreal): For impossible or past conditions",
        "Structure: particle + condition + result"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "إِنْ تَدْرُسْ تَنْجَحْ", "english": "If you study, you will succeed" },
        { "arabic": "إِذَا جَاءَ أَذْهَبُ", "english": "When he comes, I will go" },
        { "arabic": "لَوْ دَرَسَ لَنَجَحَ", "english": "If he had studied, he would have succeeded" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Types of Conditional Particles",
      "titleArabic": "أنواع أدوات الشرط",
      "content": [
        "إِنْ and إِذَا are used for real conditions (possible), while لَوْ is used for unreal/hypothetical conditions."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "إِنْ - general condition, both verbs in jussive",
        "إِذَا - certainty implied, often with past verbs",
        "لَوْ - past hypothetical, result often has لَـ prefix",
        "لَوْ دَرَسَ لَنَجَحَ (If he had studied, he would have succeeded)"
      ]
    }
  ],
